# Cursor Rules — Portfolio Rebuild

Read CLAUDE.md for full project context, content inventory, and design direction.
Reference `mockups/complete-mockup.html` for the approved visual design.

## File conventions

- Components: `src/components/ComponentName.tsx` (PascalCase)
- Data: `src/data/portfolio.ts` (single source of truth for ALL content)
- Styles: `src/app/globals.css` (design tokens, @keyframes for card animations)
- Utils: `src/lib/utils.ts` (cn() helper)
- No CSS modules. No styled-components. Tailwind only.

## Component rules

- Always add `"use client"` for components using Framer Motion, hooks, or browser APIs.
- Import motion from `"motion/react"` (NOT `"framer-motion"` — the package is `motion`).
- Pull ALL text content from `src/data/portfolio.ts`. Zero hardcoded strings in JSX.
- Use `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts` for conditional class merging.
- Every section component receives its section number as a prop or derives it internally.

### Section header pattern
Every section uses this consistent header:
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 mb-12">
  <span className="font-mono text-sm text-indigo-400">{sectionNumber}</span>
  <span className="text-[28px] font-semibold tracking-tight">{title}</span>
  <span className="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-[#1a1a1a] to-transparent" />
</div>
```

## Animation rules

### Framer Motion — for entrance/interaction animations
```tsx
// Scroll-triggered entrance (use on cards, sections)
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-50px" }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.5, delay: index * 0.1 }}
/>

// Hover lift effect (use on bento cards)
<motion.div
  whileHover={{ y: -6, borderColor: "rgba(255,255,255,0.1)" }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
/>

// Hero text stagger
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 24 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.8, delay: 0.2 * index }}
/>
```

### CSS @keyframes — for always-running background animations in cards
Put these in `globals.css`. They run continuously inside the visual area of each project/experience card. Examples: orbiting satellite, racing car, robotic arm swing, bouncing dots, typing code. These should be pure CSS for performance — Framer Motion would re-render too often.

### Animation performance
- Use `transform` and `opacity` only for CSS animations (GPU-accelerated).
- Use `will-change: transform` on elements with complex animations.
- Use `filter: blur()` sparingly — it's expensive. Only on hero orbs.

## Styling rules

### Colors (Tailwind custom or inline)
```
bg-[#050505]      — page background
bg-[#0a0a0a]      — card background
border-[#151515]  — card border default
border-[#2a2a2a]  — card border hover
text-[#f0f0f0]    — primary text
text-[#888]       — secondary text
text-[#555]       — muted text
text-[#444]       — very muted (dates, tech labels)
```

### Tag/badge colors by category
```
embedded:        bg-pink-500/10 text-pink-400 border-pink-500/15
full-stack:      bg-indigo-400/10 text-indigo-400 border-indigo-400/15
systems:         bg-green-400/10 text-green-400 border-green-400/15
machine-learning:bg-yellow-400/10 text-yellow-400 border-yellow-400/15
computer-vision: bg-cyan-400/10 text-cyan-400 border-cyan-400/15
web/hackathon:   bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-400 border-orange-400/15
robotics:        bg-green-400/10 text-green-400 border-green-400/15
networking:      bg-indigo-400/10 text-indigo-400 border-indigo-400/15
IoT:             bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-400 border-orange-400/15
parallel:        bg-cyan-400/10 text-cyan-400 border-cyan-400/15
software:        bg-indigo-400/10 text-indigo-400 border-indigo-400/15
```

### Responsive breakpoints
```
Mobile:  < 768px  — single column bento, stacked experience cards
Tablet:  768-1024 — 2-column bento, side-by-side experience
Desktop: > 1024   — 3-column bento, full layout
```

### Navbar
- Fixed position, `backdrop-blur-xl`, `bg-[#050505]/70`
- Logo: "JS." with the dot in indigo-400
- Links: text-[#555], hover text-white, transition
- No hamburger menu in desktop. Simple collapse on mobile.

### Hero
- Full viewport height (100vh)
- 4 gradient orbs with `filter: blur(120px)`, animated with CSS @keyframes (float/drift)
- Centered text: overline → h1 (with gradient span) → subtitle → CTA buttons
- Scroll indicator at bottom with pulsing line
- Staggered Framer Motion entrance (overline 0.2s, h1 0.4s, sub 0.6s, CTA 0.8s)

### Bento grid
- 3 columns on desktop, 2 on tablet, 1 on mobile
- Featured card (DUAL! game) spans 2 columns
- Each card: visual area (top, 220px height) + body area (bottom, padding)
- Visual area contains the unique CSS animation for that project
- Body area: tags → title → description → tech stack

### Experience cards
- Grid layout: date column (160px) + content column
- Subtle background animation in each card (very low opacity, doesn't distract from text)
- Tech pills at bottom of each card
- Framer Motion scroll-triggered entrance

## Commit rules
- One logical change per commit
- Imperative mood: "Add Hero component" not "Added Hero component"
- Run `npm run dev` after every change to verify
- Run `npm run lint` before pushing

## Import order
1. React / Next.js
2. Third-party libraries (motion, clsx, etc.)
3. Internal data (`@/data/portfolio`)
4. Internal components (`@/components/...`)
5. Internal utils (`@/lib/utils`)
6. Types

## What to NEVER do
- Never hardcode content in components — always use portfolio.ts
- Never use ClashDisplay font
- Never use MUI components
- Never use Three.js
- Never use the floating pill navbar from the old design
- Never use the vertical timeline from the old design
- Never put DARC or NASA in the projects section (they are experiences)
- Never use `framer-motion` import path (use `motion/react` instead)
